message.content:
Before breaking his arm, Cam could type 9 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would have typed:
9 words/minute × 5 minutes = 45 words

After breaking his arm and using his left hand, he could type 6 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would have typed:
6 words/minute × 5 minutes = 30 words

The difference between the number of words he could type before and after is:
45 words - 30 words = 15 words

So, the difference in the number of words Cam could type in 5 minutes before and after breaking his arm is 15 words.
